OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1784112473
OL,3,CHeatwave deaths: How extreme
OL,4,Ctemperatures can kill
OL,6,FBut what is the impact of heat on the
OL,7,Fhuman body, and how can it lead to
OL,8,Fdeath?
OL,10,FITV News spoke to two doctors from
OL,11,FImperial College London and the London
OL,12,FSchool of Hygiene and Tropical
OL,13,FMedicine, who, alongside the Met
OL,14,FOffice, helped conduct the research.
OL,16,FWhat effect can heat have on the human
OL,17,Fbody?
OL,19,FHeatwaves can cause heat stress, which
OL,20,Foccurs when the body struggles to
OL,21,Fregulate its temperature.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1784112473
OL,3,CHeatwave deaths: How extreme
OL,4,Ctemperatures can kill
OL,6,FEssentially, the body has to work
OL,7,Fharder in the heat to cool itself and
OL,8,Fmaintain a 37C body temperature.
OL,10,FThis "drastically reduces blood
OL,11,Fpressure as more blood is redirected
OL,12,Fto the skin, thus increasing the heart
OL,13,Frate," Dr Malcolm Mistry, Assistant
OL,14,FProfessor in Climate and Geo-spatial
OL,15,FModelling at the London School of
OL,16,FHygiene & Tropical Medicine, told ITV
OL,17,FNews.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1784112473
OL,3,CHeatwave deaths: How extreme
OL,4,Ctemperatures can kill
OL,6,FHeat can not only place enormous
OL,7,Fstrain on several organs, such as the
OL,8,Fheart and kidneys, but also causes the
OL,9,Fbody to produce sweat to help cool
OL,10,Fitself, which can then lead to fluid
OL,11,Floss, he added.
OL,13,FCan the heat cause serious illness in
OL,14,Fthe UK?
OL,16,FHeatwaves have an undeniable impact on
OL,17,Fhospital admissions across the country.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1784112473
OL,3,CHeatwave deaths: How extreme
OL,4,Ctemperatures can kill
OL,6,F"The majority of our existing housing
OL,7,Fstock, as well as public
OL,8,Finfrastructure including transport,
OL,9,Fschools, care homes and hospitals, is
OL,10,Fnot built to withstand this shift in
OL,11,Fmore severe heatwaves", Dr Mistry said.
OL,13,F"This, in turn, increases the health
OL,14,Frisk in various forms, such as from
OL,15,Fheat exhaustion to more serious
OL,16,Fheatstroke."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
