PN,31507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1784112473
OL,3,CHeatwave deaths: How extreme
OL,4,Ctemperatures can kill
OL,6,FAccording to the NHS website, heat
OL,7,Fexhaustion typically doesn't require
OL,8,Femergency assistance if you are able
OL,9,Fto cool yourself down. However, if it
OL,10,Fdevelops into heatstroke, this needs
OL,11,Fto be treated as an emergency.
OL,13,F"In addition, a surge of fatal heart
OL,14,Fattacks, renal failure, risk of
OL,15,Fpreterm births, severe psychiatric
OL,16,Femergencies, and widespread sleep
OL,17,Fdeprivation from increasingly hot
OL,18,Fnights are the other growing health
OL,19,Frisks associated with extreme heat,"
OL,20,FDr Mistry added.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1784112473
OL,3,CHeatwave deaths: How extreme
OL,4,Ctemperatures can kill
OL,6,FDehydration can also occur when your
OL,7,Fbody loses more fluids than you take
OL,8,Fin.
OL,10,FHow heat can be a "silent killer"
OL,12,FWhilst the research did not focus on
OL,13,Fspecific illnesses, according to the
OL,14,FUK Health Security Agency (UKHSA),
OL,15,Fcirculatory diseases are repeatedly
OL,16,Fthe primary cause of these deaths.
OL,18,FCirculatory diseases are a group of
OL,19,Fconditions that affect your heart and
OL,20,Fblood vessels.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31509
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1784112473
OL,3,CHeatwave deaths: How extreme
OL,4,Ctemperatures can kill
OL,6,FLast year, 409 deaths were linked to
OL,7,Fcirculatory conditions during heat
OL,8,Fepisodes.
OL,10,FOther scientific studies "point to
OL,11,Fseveral health conditions that are
OL,12,Fmost at risk from exposure to extreme
OL,13,Fheat, namely, diabetes, hypertension,
OL,14,Fcardiovascular disease and kidney
OL,15,Fdisease," said Dr Mistry.
OL,17,FWho is at the highest risk?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31510
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1784112473
OL,3,CHeatwave deaths: How extreme
OL,4,Ctemperatures can kill
OL,6,FThe burden falls heavily on older
OL,7,Fpeople, infants and children, pregnant
OL,8,Fwomen, and anyone with pre-existing
OL,9,Fhealth conditions.
OL,11,FConcerns around pre-existing health
OL,12,Fconditions
OL,14,FPeople living with pre-existing health
OL,15,Fconditions are significantly more
OL,16,Fvulnerable to high temperatures since
OL,17,Fheatwaves "directly exacerbate a wide
OL,18,Frange of chronic illnesses," according
OL,19,Fto Dr Garyfallos Konstantinoudis,
OL,20,FAssistant Professor at the Grantham
OL,21,FInstitute, Imperial College London.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31511
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1784112473
OL,3,CHeatwave deaths: How extreme
OL,4,Ctemperatures can kill
OL,6,FWhilst those with cardiovascular
OL,7,Fdisease "face a heightened risk of
OL,8,Fheart attacks and strokes", high heat
OL,9,Fcombined with poor air quality can
OL,10,Falso worsen breathing conditions, such
OL,11,Fas asthma and chronic obstructive
OL,12,Fpulmonary disease, known as COPD, he
OL,13,Fadded.
OL,15,F"Studies estimate that extreme heat
OL,16,Fcontributes to approximately 2,000
OL,17,FCOPD-related hospital admissions each
OL,18,Fyear," said Dr Konstantinoudis.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31512
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1784112473
OL,3,CHeatwave deaths: How extreme
OL,4,Ctemperatures can kill
OL,6,F"People living with dementia,
OL,7,Fdiabetes, kidney disease, and mental
OL,8,Fhealth conditions are equally at risk,
OL,9,Fas these conditions impair the body's
OL,10,Fability to recognise and respond to
OL,11,Fheat," he added.
OL,13,FAge, pregnancy and other factors
OL,15,FAccording to the NHS, those aged 65
OL,16,Fand over are an at-risk group.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31513
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1784112473
OL,3,CHeatwave deaths: How extreme
OL,4,Ctemperatures can kill
OL,6,FDr Konstantinoudis said: "As we age,
OL,7,Fthe body becomes less able to regulate
OL,8,Fits temperature effectively, while
OL,9,Fconditions such as heart disease,
OL,10,Fdementia, and respiratory illnesses,
OL,11,Fwhich are far more prevalent in older
OL,12,Fadults, are significantly worsened by
OL,13,Fheat.
OL,15,F"This vulnerability is further
OL,16,Fcompounded by social isolation,
OL,17,Freduced mobility, and medication that
OL,18,Fcan interfere with the body's ability
OL,19,Fto respond to heat, making older
OL,20,Fadults the group most at risk during
OL,21,Fheatwaves."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31514
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1784112473
OL,3,CHeatwave deaths: How extreme
OL,4,Ctemperatures can kill
OL,6,FHe added that extreme heat is known to
OL,7,Fexacerbate pre-existing health
OL,8,Fconditions, including diabetes,
OL,9,Fhypertension, cardiovascular and renal
OL,10,Fdisease, which can lead to increased
OL,11,Fmortality.
OL,13,F"Furthermore, even in a healthy older
OL,14,Fadult, one of the most important
OL,15,Fthermoregulatory mechanisms ` sweating
OL,16,F` is largely compromised, leading to a
OL,17,Fgreater risk of illness and fatalities
OL,18,Famong older people."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31515
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1784112473
OL,3,CHeatwave deaths: How extreme
OL,4,Ctemperatures can kill
OL,6,FThe NHS adds that babies and young
OL,7,Fchildren can become ill during very
OL,8,Fhot weather, as their health could be
OL,9,Fseriously affected by dehydration,
OL,10,Fheat exhaustion, heat stroke, and
OL,11,Fsunburn.
OL,13,FThe heat can also be very
OL,14,Funcomfortable for pregnant women and
OL,15,Fwomen in perimenopause, although the
OL,16,FNational Childbirth Trust has noted
OL,17,Fthat "guidance to avoid heat in
OL,18,Fpregnancy is based on limited research
OL,19,Fevidence."
OL,21,FHow can I stay safe in the heat?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31516
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1784112473
OL,3,CHeatwave deaths: How extreme
OL,4,Ctemperatures can kill
OL,6,FAlthough some groups of individuals
OL,7,Fmay be at high risk, the heat can
OL,8,Faffect anyone. Even if you are fit and
OL,9,Fhealthy, it is important to stay
OL,10,Fvigilant.
OL,12,FThe NHS describes the main risks posed
OL,13,Fby a heatwave as not drinking enough
OL,14,Fwater, overheating, heat exhaustion,
OL,15,Fand heatstroke.
OL,17,FSubscribe for free to our weekly
OL,18,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,19,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,20,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31517
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1784112473
OL,3,CHeatwave deaths: How extreme
OL,4,Ctemperatures can kill
OL,6,FThey advise sticking to the shade in
OL,7,Fthe hottest hours of the day, and
OL,8,Fwearing sunscreen, a hat, and light
OL,9,Fclothes.
OL,11,FKeeping your living space cool by
OL,12,Fclosing curtains during the day and
OL,13,Fusing an electric fan if the
OL,14,Ftemperature is below 35C is also
OL,15,Fhelpful.
OL,17,FYou can find more detailed information
OL,18,Fon how to stay safe here.
OL,20,FIn a medical emergency, always call
OL,21,F999.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
